{{Quote|Advisory: even if you can't understand gonk droids, they can understand you. Interact accordingly.|An announcement aboard the [[New Republic]] cruiser ''[[Temperance]]''|<ref name="Star Wars: Squadrons">''[[Star Wars: Squadrons]]''</ref>}}
The '''GNK-series power droid''', also known as the '''gonk droid''', was a well-known type of [[power droid]]<ref name="Databank GNK" /> manufactured by [[Industrial Automaton]].<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> They were often referred to as gonk [[droid]]s in imitation of their honking sound.<ref name="Databank GNK" /> They can often be seen around [[Tatooine]] working on [[moisture farm]]s or spaceports like [[Mos Eisley]]. Gonk droids can also be used as a table to play board games on<ref name="War-Mantle">{{TBB|War-Mantle}}</ref> or to put other equipment like a [[payment dispenser]].<ref name="KenobiI">{{Kenobi|Part I}}</ref> 

On [[Jedha]], caretakers used GNK droids to transport materials and house data; these droids would sometimes be interred along with their owners. <ref name="Star Wars: Jedi Survivor">''[[Star Wars Jedi: Survivor]]''</ref> The [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]] modified GNK units so that they acted as weapons; once deployed, those droids would march slowly across the battlefield until they collided with an enemy building and explode.<ref name="FA">''[[Star Wars: Force Arena]]''</ref>

Known GNK droids included [[4B-EG-6]],<ref name="TFA" /> [[Gonky (Uprising)|Gonky]],<ref name="Uprising" /> [[Gonky (Clone Force 99)|Gonky]] of [[Clone Force 99]],<ref name="Databank Gonky">{{Databank|gonky|Gonky}}</ref> and a gray GNK power droid that was present in [[Boba Fett's Palace|Jabba's Palace]] around [[4 ABY]], where it squealed in pain, as [[8D8]], under the command of its supervisor droid [[EV-9D9]], lowered a hot glowing iron on the soles of its feet in order to torture it.<ref name="ROTJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref>

